#######################
## Initialization

DOCUMENT();
loadMacros(
	"PGbasicmacros.pl", 
	"Parser.pl", 
	"PGcourse.pl"
	);


TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

Context("Numeric");
Context()->variables->add(n => ['Real', limits=>[1,10], resolution=>1]);

###################################
# Setup

$a=random(2,9,1);

$terms = Formula("(-1)^n/((2n+1)*$a^(2*n+1))x^(2n+1)");

$term0 = Compute(" x/$a ");
$term1 = Compute("-x^3/(3*$a^3)");
$term2 = Compute(" x^5/(5*$a^5)");
$term3 = Compute("-x^7/(7*$a^7)");
$term4 = Compute(" x^9/(9*$a^9)");

$interval = Interval("(-$a,$a)");
Context()->texStrings;


###########################################
# Problem Statement
BEGIN_TEXT

$PAR
For the following function, find the full power series centered at \(x=0\) and then give the first 5 nonzero terms of the power series and the open interval of convergence.
$PAR
\[f(x) = \tan^{-1}\left(\frac{x}{$a}\right) \]
$PAR
\( f(x) = \displaystyle \sum\limits_{n=0}^{\infty} \) \{ ans_rule() \}
$PAR
\( f(x) = \) \{ ans_rule(10) \} \(+\) \{ ans_rule(10) \} \(+\) \{ ans_rule(10) \} \(+\) \{ ans_rule(10) \} \(+\) \{ ans_rule(10) \} \(+ \cdots\) 
$PAR
The open interval of convergence is: \{ans_rule() \} (Give your answer in \{helpLink('interval notation')\}.)
END_TEXT

### Answer evaluation

Context()->normalStrings;

ANS($terms->cmp);
ANS($term0->cmp);
ANS($term1->cmp);
ANS($term2->cmp);
ANS($term3->cmp);
ANS($term4->cmp);
ANS($interval->cmp);

######################################

ENDDOCUMENT();
